'''霍利奧克'''（{{lang-en|Holyoke}}），綽號'''紙城'''，是[[美國|美國]][[麻薩諸塞州|麻薩諸塞州]][[漢登縣|漢登縣]]的一個城市，座落於康乃狄克河西岸和湯姆山脈之間。面積59.1平方公里。根據[[美國2010年人口普查|美國2010年人口普查]]，人口39,880人。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/1600000US2530840 |title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Holyoke city, Massachusetts |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |work=American Factfinder |access-date=August 2, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213111743/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/1600000US2530840 |archive-date=February 13, 2020|language=英语}}</ref> 到了 2018 年，估計人口數為 40,358。霍利奧克位於[[斯普林菲尔德_(马萨诸塞州)|斯普林菲爾德]] (Springfield) 北邊 13 公里，屬於{{Interlanguage link multi|斯普林菲爾德大都會區|en|Springfield metropolitan area, Massachusetts}} 的一部份，為麻薩諸塞州兩個截然不同的都會區之一。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=May 23, 2019|language=英语|archive-date=2017-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529192346/https://census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2016.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

霍利奧克是美國早期[[新市鎮|規劃的工業城市]]之一。霍利奧克城與霍利奧克大壩串聯，充分利用哈德利瀑布的水力，是新英格蘭少數建築於格狀規劃上的城市。<ref>{{cite book|title=Creative Economies in Post-Industrial Cities; Manufacturing a (Different) Scene|last=Breitbart|first=Myrna Margulies|publisher=Routledge|location=London and New York|year=2016|chapter='Lofty artists' vs. 'El Oro del Barrio': Crafting Community and a Sustainable Economic Future in the Paper City|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bxspDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA59|language=英语}}</ref> 在 19 世紀末期，這座城市估計產出美國 80 % 的手寫紙用量，也是美國最大造紙廠建設公司、世界最大造紙廠、絲綢廠、和羊駝毛廠的所在地。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Journal of the Boston Society of Civil Engineers|title=Emory Alexander Ellsworth|page=480|volume=III|issue=8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KhdbAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA480&lpg=PA480|date=October 1916|quote=In 1879 Mr. Ellsworth left the firm of Davis & Ellsworth to become principal assistant and head draftsman for D. H. & A. B. Tower, of Holyoke, who were the largest firm of paper mill architects in the country at that time, and who designed no less than twenty paper mills in the city of Holyoke alone|language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Root |first1=Joshua L. |date=Fall 2009 |title=Something Will Drop: Socialists, Unions and Trusts in Nineteenth-Century Holyoke |url=http://www.wsc.mass.edu/mhj/pdfs/Something%20Will%20Drop%20Holyoke%20Socialists.pdf |journal=Historic Journal of Massachusetts |volume=37 |issue=2 |page=38 |doi= |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224101501/http://www.wsc.mass.edu/mhj/pdfs/Something%20Will%20Drop%20Holyoke%20Socialists.pdf |archive-date=December 24, 2017 |language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=Silk|volume=XV|title=Who's Who in the Silk Industry–William Skinner|page=44|number=3|publisher=Silk Publishing Company|date=March 1922|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HX09AQAAMAAJ&pg=RA2-PA44|quote=One building alone is 1000 feet long—the largest silk mill, under one roof, in the world|language=英语}}</ref> 儘管如今在霍利奧克的造紙商家數量已大幅下降，人們通常還是稱它為「紙城」。<ref>{{cite book |last=Nutting |first=George M. |date=1937 |title=Massachusetts; a guide to its places and people |url=https://archive.org/stream/massachusettsgui00federich#page/248/mode/2up |location=Cambridge |publisher=The Riverside Press |page=248 |isbn= |author-link= |language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Basbanes |first=Nicholas A. |title=On Paper: The Everything of Its Two-thousand-year History |year=2014 |url=https://archive.org/details/onpapereverythin0000basb_q7l6|location=New York |publisher=Random House |page=[https://archive.org/details/onpapereverythin0000basb_q7l6/page/100 100] |isbn= 9780307279644|language=英语}}</ref> 如今，這座城市擁有一些專門的製造公司、以及麻州綠色高性能計算中心——一座於 2012 年啟用的校際研究設施。霍利奧克也是排球名人堂的所在地，被稱為是「排球的發源地」。因為這項國際性的奧林匹克運動項目是在 1895 年，在當地的[[基督教青年會|基督教青年會]] (YMCA) [[韋廉姆·G·摩根|韋廉姆·G·摩根]] 發明並首次進行的。<ref>{{cite book |editor1-last=Sullivan |editor1-first=Mark |editor2-last=Travis |editor2-first=William |date=2005 |title=Fodor's Berkshires and Pioneer Valley |location=New York |publisher=Random House |page=[https://archive.org/details/fodorsberkshires00fodo/page/124 124] |isbn=9781400014675 |language=英语}}</ref>

水力工程師{{Interlanguage link multi|克萊門斯·赫歇爾|en|Clemens Herschel}} 在 1880 年代於霍利奧克水力發電公司工作時，發明了[[文丘里效應|文丘里儀表]] 用來決定[[霍利奧克運河系統中|霍利奧克運河系統中]]各個工廠的用水。<ref>{{cite journal|page=254|volume=136|issue=3433|date=August 17, 1935|journal=Nature|doi=10.1038/136254a0|title=Invention of the Venturi Meter|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_nature-uk_1935-08-17_136_3433/page/254|bibcode=1935Natur.136Q.254.|language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Instrument Flying Handbook (FAA-H-8083-15A)|pages=5–17|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing; Federal Aviation Administration, U.S. Dept. of Transportation|series=Flight Standards Service|year=2013|url=https://books.google.com/?id=EONDCgAAQBAJ&pg=SA5-PA17&dq=#v=onepage&q=&f=false|isbn=9781616083021|language=英语}}</ref> 這款設備提供了最早能夠精確測量大規模流水的管道，如今被用在一些工程方面，包括供水系統、汽化器、以及飛行儀表。由於有這些市政運河所提供的動力，霍利奧克是該州電力價格最低的地方之一。2016 年，該城市 85% 到 90% 的電力為碳中和，並預計在未來達到 100% 碳中和的目標。<ref>{{cite news |last=Serreze |first=Mary C. |date=July 20, 2016 |title=Palmer and Holyoke honored for 100% renewable energy commitment |url=http://www.masslive.com/news/index.ssf/2016/07/palmer_and_holyoke_honored_for.html |work=MassLive |location=Springfield, Mass. |access-date=December 23, 2017 |language=英语 |archive-date=2018-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815115922/https://www.masslive.com/news/index.ssf/2016/07/palmer_and_holyoke_honored_for.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mass.gov/index.php/news/baker-polito-administration-awards-1-million-renewable-energy-grant-to-holyoke |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223202839/https://www.mass.gov/index.php/news/baker-polito-administration-awards-1-million-renewable-energy-grant-to-holyoke |date=March 11, 2017 |archive-date=December 23, 2017 |title=Baker-Polito Administration Awards $1 Million Renewable Energy Grant to Holyoke |website=MA Executive Office of Energy and Environmental Affairs |publisher=Commononwealth of Massachusetts |access-date=December 23, 2017|language=英语}}</ref>

除了來自「[[中國留美幼童|中国教育代表团]]」的交換學生以外，該城市還接待過一名重要的中國官員。1906 年 5 月，[[陳錦濤|陳錦濤]]——清朝第一名外國學者，被派來霍利奧克研究這裡萌芽中的造紙業和基礎設施，並在經過一個月的觀察後彙報給中國政府。他不只受到了工廠老闆的接待，也受到了市政府親自的接待，包括帶他參觀{{Interlanguage link multi|霍利奧克貯水系統|en|Holyoke Water Works}} 的城市工程師——詹姆斯·提格 。陳錦濤很可能是中國同盟會的一員，後來在清廷和中華民國政府繼續擔任重要職務，包括擔任後者的臨時外交部長。<ref>Boorman, Harvard L., editor, ''[https://books.google.com/books?redir_esc=y&id=KWHREtBHNqYC&q= Biographical Dictionary of the Republic of China]'', "Ch’en Chin-t’ao", Columbia University Press, New York, 1967. I:170:173. (英语)</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Visiting Holyoke Mills; Chintao Chen, Representative of the Chinese Government, Making a Special Study of the Paper Industry of Holyoke|work=Springfield Republican|page=13|date=May 24, 1906|location=Springfield, Mass.|language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|journal=[[Journal_of_Race_Development|Journal of Race Development]]|volume=4|issue=1|page=103|title=The Relation of the Returned Students to the Chinese Revolution|last=Tsao|first=Y. S.|quote=Very few students from Europe and America were members of the 'Tung Men Hwei,' [sic] and judging from their actions only Mr. C. T. Wang, Drs. Chen Hui Wang and Chintao Chen from Yale were the only possible ones|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LN2Aa5DnYYYC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103|year=1914|language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Flood Prevention in China|quote=Dr. Chen Chin-Tao is now on his way to America to represent his country in negotiations [for $20,000,000 of bonds for engineering work to prevent floods in the Huai River Valley]|page=63|volume=2|issue=5|magazine=Santa Fe Trail Magazine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=apJFAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA3-PA63|date=May 1914|language=英语}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|journal=American Journal of International Law; Supplement- Official Documents|page=117|title=Exchange of Notes- Memorandum handed by the Japanese Minister to Dr. Chen Chintao, Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs|volume=11|year=1917|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=New York|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E3YLAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA117|language=英语}}</ref>

